## Adobe Marketo

Connector ID (`connector.id` in the resource): `adobemarketoConnector`

Properties (used under the `properties` block in the resource as a key in the JSON object):

* `addLeadsArray` (string): Enter the unique ID of the leads to add to the list. Separate multiple values with a comma, such as "456123,987654". Console display name: "Lead IDs".
* `bodyData` (string): The body of the API call. Console display name: "Body".
* `clientId` (string): Your Adobe Marketo client ID. Console display name: "Client ID".
* `clientSecret` (string): Your Adobe Marketo client secret. Console display name: "Client Secret".
* `customAttributes` (string): Additional attributes. Console display name: "Custom Attributes".
* `customEndpoint` (string): This endpoint is added to the base API URL selected in the connector configuration. Remeber to removed "rest/" from the endpoint. Console display name: "Custom Endpoint".
* `customQueryParams` (string): Query parameters for the request. Console display name: "Query Parameters".
* `email` (string): The user's email address. Console display name: "Email".
* `endpoint` (string): The API endpoint for your Adobe Marketo instance, such as "abc123.mktorest.com/rest". Console display name: "API URL".
* `firstName` (string): The user's first name. Console display name: "First Name".
* `folderList` (string): Select the folder that contains the lists you want information about. Console display name: "Folder".
* `headers` (string): Define additional headers to send to Adobe Marketo. For help, see the API documentation. Console display name: "Additional Headers".
* `lastName` (string): The user's last name. Console display name: "Last Name".
* `leadId` (string): The unique identifier for the lead, such as "318581". Console display name: "Lead ID".
* `listId` (string): The unique ID for the list, such as "56789". Console display name: "List ID".
* `listName` (string): Enter a name for the new list. Console display name: "List Name".
* `method` (string): The HTTP method of the API call. Console display name: "HTTP Method".
* `middleName` (string): The user's middle name. Console display name: "Middle Name".
* `phone` (string): The user's phone number. Console display name: "Phone Number".
* `searchColumn` (string): Select the Marketo lead attribute that you want to search. Console display name: "Search Attribute".
* `searchLeadArray` (string): Enter the values to look for in the search attribute. Separate multiple values with a comma, such as "138273,jsmith@example.com". Console display name: "Search Values".
* `searchListId` (string): The unique ID for the list, such as "56789". Console display name: "List ID".
* `searchListMethod` (string): Select “Use List ID” or “Use List Name” to get information about a single list, or select a folder to get information about all lists within it. Console display name: "Search Type".
* `searchListName` (string): The name of the list to get information about, such as "Founders". Console display name: "List Name".
* `smartListToggle` (string): Select the type of list you are reading. Smart lists support additional accuracy and functionality. Console display name: "List Type".


