## Amazon DynamoDB

Connector ID (`connector.id` in the resource): `connectorAmazonDynamoDB`

Properties (used under the `properties` block in the resource as a key in the JSON object):

* `attrDefinitions` (string): A list of JSON objects containing AttributeName and AttributeType (ex.  [{ AttributeName: 'name', AttributeType 'S'}, {AttributeName: 'age', AttributeType 'N'}] ). Console display name: "List of Attribute Name and Type".
* `attrKeySchema` (string): A list of JSON objects containing AttributeName and KeyType (ex.  [{ AttributeName: 'name', KeyType: 'HASH'}, {AttributeName: 'age', KeyType 'RANGE'}] ). Console display name: "List of Attribute Name and Key Type".
* `awsAccessKey` (string): Your AWS Access Key. Console display name: "AWS Access Key".
* `awsAccessSecret` (string): Access Secret corresponding with Access Key found in Your Security Credentials. Console display name: "AWS Access Secret".
* `awsRegion` (string): The AWS Region you are using the connector for. Console display name: "AWS Region".
* `condtionalExpression` (string): A condition that must be satisfied in order for a conditional update to succeed. Console display name: "Conditional Expression".
* `convertClassInstanceToMap` (string): Whether to convert typeof object to map attribute. Console display name: "Convert Class Instance To Map".
* `convertEmptyValues` (string): Whether to automatically convert empty strings, blobs, and sets to `null`. Console display name: "Convert Empty Values".
* `expressionAttributeNames` (string): Use if your attribute names have conflicts with keywords or you'd like to use placeholders for attribute names. Console display name: "Expression Attribute Names".
* `expressionAttributeValues` (string): One or more values that can be substituted in an expression. Console display name: "Expression Attribute Values".
* `filterExpression` (string): Conditions applied after a Query but before the data is returned. (See connector documentation for further info on FilterExpression). Console display name: "Filter Expression".
* `indexName` (string): The name of an index to query. This index can be any local secondary index or global secondary index on the table. Console display name: "Index Name".
* `itemsJSON` (string): A code field to enter JSON object.  Console display name: "Items (JSON format)".
* `itemsKV` (string): A key-value list of the Attribute-Value pairs of the item. NOTE: All values must be strings. Console display name: "Items Key/Value List".
* `keyConditionExpression` (string): The condition that specifies the key values for items to be retrieved by the Query action. Console display name: "Key Condition Expression".
* `keyJSON` (string): A code field to enter JSON object.  Console display name: "Key of Item (JSON format)".
* `keyKV` (string): A key-value list of the Attribute-Value pairs of the item. NOTE: All values must be strings. Console display name: "Key of Item".
* `limit` (string): The number of results returned by your query (MAX 1MB dataset; if reach MAX returns LastEvaluatedKey). Console display name: "Limit".
* `projectionExpression` (string): A string that identifies one or more attributes to retrieve from the table.  Console display name: "Projection Expression".
* `removeUndefinedValues` (string): Whether to remove undefined values while marshalling. Console display name: "Remove Undefined Values".
* `sdkCommandName` (string): The name of the SDK command you want to call (ex. getObject, createBucket). Console display name: "SDK Custom Call Command Name".
* `sdkParameters` (string): A key value list that will create a JSON object that will be passed as the arguments for your custom command. Console display name: "SDK Custom Call Parameters".
* `tableName` (string): The name of the Table. Console display name: "Table Name".
* `updateExpression` (string): The update expression (ex. ' set info.plot = 'the plot', info.rank = 'the rank' '). Console display name: "Update Expression Clause".
* `wrapNumbers` (string): Whether to return numbers as a string instead of converting them to native JavaScript numbers. Console display name: "Wrap Numbers".


