* `searchScreenTitle` (string): The main title in the Search screen. Defaults to 'Search for your income source'. Console display name: "Title in the Search screen".
* `showBackToSearchButton` (string): If set to false, hides the Return to search button in the success screen. Console display name: "Show Return to search button".
* `showCategories` (string): Show/hide category tabs (e.g. All, Employer, Gig, Payroll). Console display name: "Show category tabs".
* `showCloseButton` (string): Toggles the visibility of the Close button. This flag works only on the web implementation of Argyle Link (and not on the mobile SDKs). Console display name: "Show Close button".
* `userId` (string): Console display name: "User ID".
* `userToken` (string): User tokens are temporary access keys that let you start Argyle Link for an existing user. They are JWT tokens that contain an expiry date you can use to determine if you need to create a new user token. Newly issued tokens expire in 30 days. Console display name: "Existing user token".


