* `clientsGet_page_number` (string): Search by Page Number. Example - 1. Console display name: "PageNumber".
* `clientsGet_page_size` (string): Search by Page Size. Example - 100. Console display name: "PageSize".
* `clientsGet_search_by` (string): Search by the name of the eDiscovery Download Client. Example - Client1. Console display name: "SearchBy".
* `clientsGet_sort_by` (string): Key to sort the results. You can sort by: name/clientVersion/cplatform/createdBy. Console display name: "SortBy".
* `clientsGet_sort_order` (string): Specify the parameter by which you intend to sort the listed results. Sorting can be done in ascending or descending order. Console display name: "SortOrder".
* `createNewJob_createDownloadJobRequest_CreateDownloadJobRequest_clientName` (string): Name of the eDiscovery Download Client. Example - Client1. Console display name: "ClientName".
* `createNewJob_createDownloadJobRequest_CreateDownloadJobRequest_createdBy` (string): Name of administrator triggering the job. Example - Ernie Carter. Console display name: "CreatedBy".
* `createNewJob_createDownloadJobRequest_CreateDownloadJobRequest_custodianEmails` (string): Console display name: "CustodianEmails".
* `createNewJob_createDownloadJobRequest_CreateDownloadJobRequest_downloadLocation` (string): Location to download the job. Example - D:\Downloads. Console display name: "DownloadLocation".
* `createNewJob_createDownloadJobRequest_CreateDownloadJobRequest_downloadOption` (string): 0 indicates only metadata, 1 indicates data and metadata and 2 indicates zip download option. Console display name: "DownloadOption".
* `createNewJob_createDownloadJobRequest_CreateDownloadJobRequest_enable_data_integrity` (string): Use &#39;true&#39; to enable data integrity and &#39;false&#39; to disable data integrity. Console display name: "Enable_data_integrity".
* `createNewJob_createDownloadJobRequest_CreateDownloadJobRequest_legalholdId` (string): Legal Hold ID for which download is to be triggered. Example -10. Console display name: "LegalholdId".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_device_id` (string): Filter to get list of last successful backups for a particular device using its unique ID. Get the ID of a device using the ‘List all devices’ API.  Console display name: "DeviceID".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_last_successful` (string): Provides details of the last successful backup for a device.  Currently, only 'True' is the supported value for this parameter. Console display name: "LastSuccessful".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_max_backup_end_time` (string): Filter to list successful backups that ended before a particular date and time. Format - YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ. Console display name: "MaxBackupEndTime".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_max_backup_start_time` (string): Filter to list successful backups that started before a particular date and time. Format - YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ. Console display name: "MaxBackupStartTime".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_min_backup_end_time` (string): Filter to list successful backups that ended after a particular date and time. Format - YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ. Console display name: "MinBackupEndTime".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_min_backup_start_time` (string): Filter to list successful backups that started after a particular date and time. Format - YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ. Console display name: "MinBackupStartTime".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_page_token` (string): The token to access the next page of results. Use the token value received in the previous response's parameter 'nextPageToken'. Console display name: "PageToken".
* `endpointsV1BackupsGet_user_id` (string): Filter to get list of last successful backups on devices owned by a particular user using their user ID. Get the ID of a user using the ‘List all users’ API. Console display name: "UserID".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsGet_device_identifier` (string): Specify the unique id of the device for the selected deviceIdentifierType in inSync. Console display name: "DeviceIdentifier".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsGet_device_identifier_type` (string): Filter to list device mappings using the unique device identifier type of the device.(serial-number, uuid, or hostname). Console display name: "DeviceIdentifierType".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsGet_email_id` (string): Filter to list device mappings using the email address of a user. Console display name: "EmailID".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsGet_restore_data` (string): Filter to list device mappings using the type of data restore performed. Console display name: "RestoreData".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsMappingIDDelete_mapping_id` (string): The id associated with the device mapping. Get the mapping id by running the List Device Mapping API. Console display name: "MappingID".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsPost_endpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_EndpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_deviceIdentifier` (string): Specify the unique device identifier for the selected type. (serial-number, uuid, or hostname). Console display name: "DeviceIdentifier".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsPost_endpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_EndpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_deviceIdentifierType` (string): Specify the unique device identifier type of the device.(serial-number, uuid, or hostname). Console display name: "DeviceIdentifierType".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsPost_endpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_EndpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_deviceName` (string): Specify the name of the device that is registered with the user. Example - Ernie Carter&#39;s Macbook. Console display name: "DeviceName".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsPost_endpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_EndpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_emailID` (string): Specify the email address of the user. Example - ernie.carter@druva.com. Console display name: "EmailID".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsPost_endpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_EndpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_oldDeviceName` (string): Name of the user&#39;s old device in Druva inSync that is to be replaced with a new device.   :fa-info-circle: Note: Specify the value for this parameter only if you want to replace the device for the user, else keep this field blank. Console display name: "OldDeviceName".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsPost_endpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_EndpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_restoreData` (string): The type of data restore to be performed.(ALL, SYSTEM, OR DATA)  Type of data to be restored on the new device.Specify one of the following value:  1) All - To restore both, the data and the system settings from the existing device on the new device. 2) SYSTEM - To restore only the system settings from the existing device on the new device. 3)DATA - To restore only the data from the existing device on the new device.  :fa-info-circle: Note: Specify the value for this parameter only if you want to replace the device for the user, else keep this field blank. Console display name: "RestoreData".
* `endpointsV1DevicemappingsPost_endpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_EndpointsV1DevicemappingsGetRequest_userName` (string): Specify the username of the user in Druva inSync. Example - Ernie Carter. Console display name: "UserName".
