## Freshservice

Connector ID (`connector.id` in the resource): `connectorFreshservice`

Properties (used under the `properties` block in the resource as a key in the JSON object):

* `address` (string): Address of the requester. Console display name: "Address".
* `apiKey` (string): Your Freshservice API key. Console display name: "API Key".
* `backgroundInformation` (string): Background information of the requester. Console display name: "Background Information".
* `canSeeAllTicketsFromAssociatedDepts` (string): Set to true if the requester must be allowed to view tickets filed by other members of the department, and false otherwise. Console display name: "Can See All Tickets From Associate Departments".
* `ccEmails` (string): Email address added in the 'cc' field of the incoming ticket email. Must be comma-separated list of emails. Console display name: "CC Emails (comma-separated)".
* `departmentIds` (string): Unique IDs of the departments associated with the requester.  Must be comma-separated. Console display name: "DepartmentIds (comma-separated)".
* `description` (string): HTML content of the ticket. Console display name: "Description".
* `domain` (string): Your Freshservice domain. Example: https://domain.freshservice.com/. Console display name: "Domain".
* `dueBy` (string): Timestamp that denotes when the ticket is due to be resolved. Console display name: "Due By".
* `email` (string): Email address of the requester. If no contact exists with this email address in Freshservice, it will be added as a new contact. Console display name: "Email".
* `emailConfigId` (string): ID of email config which is used for this ticket. (i.e., support@yourcompany.com/sales@yourcompany.com) If product_id is given and email_config_id is not given, product's primary email_config_id will be set. Console display name: "Email Config ID".
* `firstName` (string): First name of the requester. Console display name: "First Name".
* `frDueBy` (string): Timestamp that denotes when the first response is due. Console display name: "FR Due By".
* `groupId` (string): ID of the group to which the ticket has been assigned. The default value is the ID of the group that is associated with the given email_config_id. Console display name: "Group ID".
* `impact` (string): Ticket impact. Console display name: "Impact".
* `jobTitle` (string): Job title of the requester. Console display name: "Job Title".
* `language` (string): Language used by the requester. The default language is “en” (English). https://support.freshservice.com/support/solutions/articles/232303-list-of-languages-supported-in-freshservice. Console display name: "Language".
* `lastName` (string): Last name of the connector. Console display name: "Last Name".
* `locationId` (string): Unique ID of the location associated with the requester. Console display name: "Location ID".
* `mobilePhoneNumber` (string): Mobile phone number of the requester. Console display name: "Mobile Phone Number".
* `name` (string): Name of the requester. Console display name: "Name".
* `phone` (string): Phone number of the requester. If no contact exists with this phone number in Freshservice, it will be added as a new contact. If the phone number is set and the email address is not, then the name attribute is mandatory. Console display name: "Phone".
* `primaryEmail` (string): Primary email address of the requester. Console display name: "Primary Email".
* `priority` (string): Priority of the ticket. The default value is 1. Console display name: "Priority".
* `reportingManagerId` (string): User ID of the requester's reporting manager. Console display name: "Reporting Manager ID".
* `requesterId` (string): User ID of the requester. Console display name: "Requester ID".
* `responderId` (string): ID of the agent to whom the ticket has been assigned. Console display name: "Responder ID".
