Properties (used under the `properties` block in the resource as a key in the JSON object):

* `action` (string): The administrative action to take on the device. Console display name: "Action".
* `additionalUserProperties` (string): Define additional attributes to add to the user account. For help, see the User Accounts section of the Google Workspace SDK documentation. Console display name: "Other User Attributes".
* `bodyData` (string): The body of the API call. Console display name: "Body".
* `customerId` (string): The unique ID for the customer's Google Workspace account, such as "C123abc4d". This ID is available from the "Get User Information" capability. Console display name: "Customer ID".
* `deviceProjection` (string): The level of information to request about the device. "Basic" returns a standard set of fields. "Full" returns all fields. Console display name: "Requested Device Fields".
* `endpoint` (string): The Workspace API endpoint, such as "https://admin.googleapis.com/admin/directory/v1/users/user@example.com". Console display name: "Endpoint".
* `familyName` (string): The user's last name.  Console display name: "Family Name".
* `givenName` (string): The user's given name. Console display name: "Given Name".
* `groupKey` (string): The group's primary email address, unique group id, or alias. Console display name: "Group Identifier".
* `headersForm` (string): Define additional headers to send to Workspace. For help, see the Google Workspace API documentation. Console display name: "Additional Headers".
* `iss` (string): The email address associated with the Google Workspace service, such as "google-workspace-admin@xenon-set-123456.iam.gserviceaccount.com". Console display name: "Service Account Email Address".
* `licenseUserId` (string): The user's primary email address. Console display name: "User ID".
* `maxResults` (string): The maximum number of results to return from the query, up to 100. Console display name: "Maximum Number of Results".
* `memberDeliverySettings` (string): The member's email delivery frequency.  Console display name: "Member Email Delivery Settings".
* `memberEmail` (string): The member's email address. The member can be a user or another group. Console display name: "Member Email".
* `memberKey` (string): Identifies the group member in the API request. Console display name: "Member Key".
* `memberRole` (string): The role to assign the member in the group. Console display name: "Member Role".
* `memberType` (string): The type of member in the group. Console display name: "Member Type".
* `method` (string): The HTTP method of the API call. Console display name: "HTTP Method".
* `orderBy` (string): The device property to use for sorting results. Console display name: "Device Order".
* `pageToken` (string): The token used to specify the next page in the results, such as "3". Use this to get pages of results for queries that return more than the maximum number of results.
 Console display name: "Page Token".
* `paramsForm` (string): Query parameters for the request. Console display name: "Query Parameters".
* `password` (string): The password to assign to the user account. Console display name: "Password".
* `primaryEmail` (string): The user's primary email address. Console display name: "Primary Email".
* `privateKey` (string): The private key associated with the public key that you added to the Google Workspace service. Console display name: "Private Key".
* `productId` (string): The product ID, such as "Google-Apps". Console display name: "Product ID".
* `projection` (string): The level of information to request about the user. "Basic" returns a standard set of fields. "Full" returns all fields. "Use Custom Field Schemas" returns the Basic fields as well as specific fields associated with the schemas you enter in "Custom Field Schemas". Console display name: "Requested Fields".
* `query` (string): The query used to search for devices, such as "status:approved" or "os:Android". For help, see documentation for "Mobile device search fields" section of the Google Workspace SDK Directory API documentation.
 Console display name: "Query String".
* `resourceId` (string): The device ID, such as "AFiQxQ-WO…YM-hf080OZy". Console display name: "Device ID".
* `skuId` (string): The SKU ID, such as "Google-Apps-For-Business". Console display name: "SKU ID".
* `sortOrder` (string): The sort order for the list of devices. This is required if you have selected a "Device Order" option. Console display name: "Sort Order".
* `sub` (string): The administrator's email address. Console display name: "Admin Email Address".
* `userCustomFieldMask` (string): The list of schemas to request. This returns all fields associated with the listed schemas. Type a schema name and press Enter to add it. Console display name: "Custom Field Schemas".
* `userFieldMask` (string): The list of fields for the connector to output to the flow, such as "emails" or "emails.address". Instead of outputting all of the results from the "Requested Attributes", you can filter the results to a list of specific fields. Type a field name and press Enter to add it. Leave this field blank to include all requested fields in the connector output. Console display name: "Output Filter".
* `userKey` (string): The user's primary email address, unique user id, or one of the user's alias email addresses.
 Console display name: "User Identifier".
* `viewType` (string): The type of fields to request. "Admin View" returns publicly visible and administrator-only fields. "Public View" only returns publicly visible fields. Console display name: "View Type".


