* `assignee` (string): The person to assign the issue to. For a dynamic value, select Use Assignee ID and enter a value in the Assignee ID field. Console display name: "Assignee".
* `assigneeId` (string): The ID of the assignee, such as "5b10a2844c20165700ede21g". Console display name: "Assignee ID".
* `bodyData` (string): The body of the API call. Console display name: "Body".
* `components` (string): The ID of the component to associate with the issue, such as "10000". Console display name: "Components".
* `customQueryParams` (string): Define additional query parameters to send to Jira. For help, see the Jira Cloud platform REST API documentation. Console display name: "Query Parameters".
* `description` (string): The issue description, such as "Please fix the following development workflow issue…". Console display name: "Description".
* `dueDate` (string): The due date for the issue, formatted as "2022-01-30". Console display name: "Due Date".
* `email` (string): Email used for your Jira account. Console display name: "Email Address".
* `endpoint` (string): The Jira API endpoint, such as /rest/api/3/search. Console display name: "Endpoint".
* `expand` (string): Additional information to get for the issues returned in the results, such as "names", "schema", or "changelog". For help, see "Search for issues with JQL (POST)" in the Jira Cloud platform REST API documentation. Console display name: "Expanded Information".
* `fields` (string): The fields to get for each issue returned in the results, such as "assignee" or "comment". Type a field name and press enter to add it. Console display name: "Fields".
* `fieldsByKeys` (string): Enable this when the "Fields" list uses keys, rather than IDs, to identify fields. Console display name: "Identify Fields with Keys".
* `fixVersions` (string): The ID of the fix version to associate with the issue, such as "10001". Type an ID and press Enter to add it. Console display name: "Fix Versions".
* `headers` (string): Additional headers for the request, connector automatically adds 'Authorization' and 'Content-Type' headers. Console display name: "Additional Headers".
* `issueId` (string): The ID of the issue, such as "PROJ-1". Console display name: "Issue ID".
* `issueType` (string): The type of issue to create. Console display name: "Issue Type".
* `jql` (string): The JQL query used to search for issues, such as "project=SysAdmin AND assignee=jsmith". For help, see documentation for the Jira Query Language. Console display name: "JQL Query".
* `labels` (string): The labels to associate with the issue. Type a label and press enter to add it. Console display name: "Labels".
* `loopingTransition` (string): Enable this for transitions that start and end on the same status. Console display name: "Looping Transition".
* `maxResults` (number): The maximum number of results to return from the query. Use with Starting Result Number to get pages of results for queries that return more than the maximum number of results. Console display name: "Maximum Number of Results".
* `method` (string): The HTTP method of the API call. Console display name: "HTTP Method".
* `otherAttributes` (string): Add other attributes and their values. Will overwrite attributes in General tab if key is the same. Console display name: "Other Attributes".
* `parent` (string): The ID of an existing issue, such as "PROJ-10". When this value is provided, the new issue will be created as a sub-task of the parent issue. Console display name: "Parent Issue ID".
* `priority` (string): The priority for the issue, such as "3". Console display name: "Priority".
* `project` (string): The Jira project to create the issue in. For a dynamic value, select Use Project Key and enter a value in the Project Key field. Console display name: "Project".
* `projectKey` (string): The Jira project to create the issue in, such as "PROJ". Console display name: "Project Key".
* `queryParams` (string): Define additional query parameters to send to Jira. For help, see the Jira Cloud platform REST API documentation. Console display name: "Query Parameters".
* `reporter` (string): The person reporting the issue. For a dynamic value, select Use Reporter ID and enter a value in the Reporter ID field. Console display name: "Reporter".
* `reporterId` (string): The ID of the reporter, such as "5b10a2844c20165700ede21g". Console display name: "Reporter ID".
* `searchProperties` (string): The app or entity properties to get for each issue returned in the results. Type a property name and press enter to add it, to a maximum of five properties. Console display name: "Properties".
* `startAt` (number): The index number of the first item to return in the results. For example, "101" will return the maximum number of results starting with result number 101. Use this to get pages of results for queries that return more than the maximum number of results. Console display name: "Starting Result Number".
* `summary` (string): The issue summary, such as "Fix development workflow". Console display name: "Summary".
* `transitionId` (string): The ID of the transition to trigger. Console display name: "Transition ID".
* `updateIssueType` (string): The updated issue type. Console display name: "Issue Type".
* `updateSummary` (string): The issue summary, such as "Fix development workflow". Console display name: "Summary".
* `validateQuery` (string): The method to use to validate the JQL query. Console display name: "Query Validation".
* `versions` (string): The ID of the version to associate with the issue, such as "10001". Type an ID and press Enter to add it. Console display name: "Versions".


