## LexisNexis

Connector ID (`connector.id` in the resource): `lexisnexisV2Connector`

Properties (used under the `properties` block in the resource as a key in the JSON object):

* `apiKey` (string): Your LexisNexis API key, such as “o3x9ywfs26rm1zvl”. Console display name: "API Key".
* `apiUrl` (string): The API URL to target. For a custom value, select Use Custom API URL and enter a value in the Custom API URL field. Console display name: "API URL".
* `customAttribute` (string): Define additional parameters to send to LexisNexis, such as user attributes. For a list of valid parameters, see the LexisNexis documentation or speak to a LexisNexis representative. Console display name: "Additional Parameters".
* `customCSS` (string): Customize the CSS for the user-facing interface. Console display name: "CSS".
* `customDeliveryMethod` (string): Select a variable from your flow to dynamically set the OTP method. The value of the variable must be “email”, “sms”, or “voice”. Console display name: "Dynamic Delivery Method".
* `customHTML` (string): Customize the HTML for the user-facing interface. Console display name: "HTML".
* `customProfilingUrl` (string): The URL for the device profiling script, such as “https://h.online-metrix.net/fp/tags.js”. Console display name: "Custom Profiling URL".
* `customRequiredParameter` (string): The key for the required parameter to send to LexisNexis, such as “account_email”. Console display name: "Custom Required Parameter".
* `customScript` (string): Write custom JavaScript. Caution: Custom code is for advanced users only. Before using custom code, review the security risks in the DaVinci documentation by searching for "Using custom code safely". Console display name: "Script".
* `ddpProfilingUrl` (string): The source of the device profiling script. For a custom value, select Use Custom Profiling URL and enter a value in the Custom Profiling URL field. Console display name: "DDP Profiling URL".
* `deliveryMethod` (string): The method to use to deliver the OTP. To change the method dynamically, select Use Dynamic Delivery Method and provide a variable in the Dynamic Delivery Method field. Console display name: "Delivery Method".
* `email` (string): The user's email address, such as “jsmith@example.com”. Console display name: "Email".
* `emailBody` (string): The body of the email message containing the OTP, such as “Your one-time passcode is:${LineBreak}${OTP}${LineBreak}If you did not make this request, contact your administrator.”. The ${ExpirePeriod} variable uses the value from the OTP Timeout field. Console display name: "Email Body".
* `emailTitle` (string): The title of the email message containing the OTP, such as “Your one-time passcode”. Console display name: "Email Title".
* `events_type` (string): Select the LexisNexis event type to use. Console display name: "Event Type".
* `htmlConfig` (string): Console display name: "".
* `htmlConfig1` (string): Console display name: "".
* `loadingText` (string): The message to show when collecting the device profile. Console display name: "Device Profiling Message".
* `orgId` (string): Your LexisNexis organization ID, such as “4en6ll2s”. Console display name: "Organization ID".
* `otpLength` (string): The number of digits in the OTP. Console display name: "OTP Length".
* `otpTimeout` (string): The amount of time in minutes that the OTP is valid. Console display name: "OTP Timeout".
* `phoneNumber` (string): The user's phone number, including country code, such as “1-604-697-7040”. Console display name: "Phone Number".
* `policy` (string): The name of the Dynamic Decision Platform policy to use, such as “OTP”. The policy determines which LexisNexis service is used, such as ThreatMetrix, Emailage, or Phone Finder. You can find the policy names in your LexisNexis portal. Names are case sensitive. Console display name: "Policy".
* `queryType` (string): Select the Query type to use. Console display name: "Query Type".
* `requiredParameter` (string): Select the main parameter to send to LexisNexis, then provide the value in the Required Parameter Value field. You can optionally provide more parameters in Additional Parameters. For a dynamic value, select Use Custom Required Parameter and enter a value in the Custom Required Parameter field. Console display name: "Required Parameter".
* `requiredParameterValue` (string): Enter the value for the Required Parameter, such as "A-123456C". Console display name: "Required Parameter Value".
* `review_status` (string): Select the fallback review status to use when LexisNexis reports that no device profiling session exists. This happens when the device profiling script is blocked or times out. Console display name: "Review Status for Unknown Sessions".
* `service_type` (string): Select the LexisNexis service to use. Console display name: "Service Type".
* `session_id` (string): The unique ID associated with the device profile, provided by the Get Device Profile capability. Console display name: "Session Id".
* `smsMessage` (string): The body of the SMS message containing the OTP, such as “Your one-time passcode is:${LineBreak}${OTP}${LineBreak}If you did not make this request, contact your administrator.”. Limited to 160 ASCII characters. The ${ExpirePeriod} variable uses the value from the OTP Timeout field. Console display name: "SMS Message".
* `timeOut` (string): The maximum amount of time in seconds to allow the device profiling script to run, such as “5”. If you frequently get “unknown session” results from the DDP capability, consider increasing this time. The value must be from 1-30. Console display name: "Timeout".
* `useCustomApiURL` (string): The API URL to target, such as “https://h.online-metrix.net”. Console display name: "Custom API URL".
* `validationRules` (string): Rules to check to validate form inputs. Console display name: "Form Validation Rules".


