* `body` (string): The raw JSON body. Console display name: "Body".
* `domainEvent` (string): The type of domain event to return (see connector documentation for complete list of event types). Console display name: "Domain Event".
* `domainEventDuration` (string): Period of time for the desired event, e.g. 15h, 1d, 2m, etc. (optional). Console display name: "Domain Event Duration".
* `emailBcc` (string): Same as the “To” parameter but for bcc. You can use commas to separate multiple recipients. (optional). Console display name: "BCC".
* `emailCc` (string): Same as the “To” parameter but for cc. You can use commas to separate multiple recipients. (optional). Console display name: "CC".
* `emailSubject` (string): Subject of the email. Console display name: "Subject".
* `emailTag` (string): Tag string. (optional). Console display name: "Tag".
* `emailText` (string): Body of the email. (text version). Console display name: "Message".
* `endpoint` (string): Mailgun API endpoints, e.g. "/lists/MAILING_LIST@email.com/members" etc... Console display name: "Endpoint".
* `fromAddress` (string): Sender email address with the desired domain (e.g. YOU@YOUR_DOMAIN_NAME). Console display name: "From Address".
* `fromName` (string): Name of the sender (e.g. John Smith). Console display name: "Sender Name".
* `headers` (string): Add HTTP headers and provide their values. Console display name: "Headers".
* `mailgunDomain` (string): Name of the desired domain (e.g. mail.mycompany.com). Console display name: "Domain".
* `mailingListAccessLevel` (string): The access level of the mailing list. Either: readonly (default), members, everyone. Console display name: "Access Level".
* `mailingListAddress` (string): A valid email address for the mailing list, e.g. developers@mailgun.com. Console display name: "Mailing List Address".
* `mailingListDescription` (string): A brief description for the mailing list. (optional). Console display name: "Description".
* `mailingListMemberAddress` (string): Valid email address of the new member, e.g. new.member@gmail.com. Console display name: "Member Address".
* `mailingListMemberAttributes` (string): JSON-encoded dictionary string for arbitrary attributes of the specified member. Console display name: "Member Attributes".
* `mailingListMemberName` (string): Name of the member. (optional). Console display name: "Member Name".
* `mailingListMemberSubscriptionStatus` (string): Toggle the switch "on" to add as subscribed, leave the switch "off" to set as unsubscribed. Console display name: "Member Subscription Status".
* `mailingListMemberUpsert` (string): Toggle the switch "on" to enable updating a member if present, leave the switch "off" to raise an error in case of a duplicate member. Console display name: "Member Upsert Permissons".
* `mailingListName` (string): Mailing list name, e.g. Developers. (optional). Console display name: "Name".
* `mailingListReplyPreference` (string): Set where replies should go: “list” (default) or “sender”. (optional). Console display name: "Reply Preference".
* `method` (string): The HTTP Method. Console display name: "Method".
* `newMailingListMemberAddress` (string): New valid email address of the member, e.g. new.member@gmail.com (optional). Console display name: "New Member Address".
* `queryParameters` (string): Add query parameters and provide their values. Console display name: "Query Parameters".
* `toAddress` (string): Email address of the recipient(s). You can use commas to separate multiple recipients. Console display name: "To Address".


