## String

Connector ID (`connector.id` in the resource): `stringsConnector`

Properties (used under the `properties` block in the resource as a key in the JSON object):

* `concatenateDelimiter` (string): The optional string to include between each concatenated value, such as ", " or "-". Console display name: "Delimiter".
* `concatenateInput` (string): The string to process. Enter a string or select a string value from your flow. Console display name: "Input String".
* `dataTypeTo` (string): Select the data type to change the input value to. Console display name: "Change to".
* `decodeMethod` (string): The decoding format applied to the input string. Console display name: "String Decode Method".
* `delimiter` (string): The unique character used to separate strings. Console display name: "Delimiter".
* `encodeMethod` (string): The encoding format applied to the input string. Console display name: "String Encode Method".
* `finalDelimiter` (string): When enabled, the delimiter is also included at the end of the concatenated string. Console display name: "Include Final Delimiter".
* `finder` (string): The substring to process. Enter a string or select a string value from your flow. Console display name: "Find Substring".
* `inputValue` (string): The value to process. Enter a string or select a string value from your flow. Console display name: "Input String".
* `isAlphaNumeric` (string): By default, generated strings are a mix of uppercase and lowercase letters. When enabled, the string also includes numbers. Console display name: "Include Numbers".
* `isRegex` (string): By default, the value in the Search field is used for simple matching. When enabled, the value in the Search field must be formatted as a regular expression such as "/<expression>/g". Console display name: "Search Using Regex?".
* `length` (number): Enter the number of characters you want in the string, such as "15". Console display name: "String Length".
* `newToken` (string): When a match is found, the text identified by the Search field is replaced with this string. Console display name: "New String Value".
* `oldToken` (string): The text to search for in the original string value. For simple matching, enter literal text, such as "test". For more complex matching, enter a valid regular expression and enable Search Using Regex. For example, entering "/te[xs]t/g" matches both "test" and "text". Console display name: "Search".
* `originalValue` (string): The string to process. Enter a string or select a string value from your flow. Console display name: "Input Value".
* `replaceMode` (string): Determines whether the first match or all matches are replaced with the new value. Console display name: "Replace Mode".
* `shouldTrim` (string): When enabled, removes any white space at the beginning or end of the input string. Console display name: "Trim White Space".


