## TMT Analysis

Connector ID (`connector.id` in the resource): `tmtConnector`

Properties (used under the `properties` block in the resource as a key in the JSON object):

* `apiKey` (string): API Key for TMT Analysis. Console display name: "API Key".
* `apiSecret` (string): API Secret for TMT Analysis. Console display name: "API Secret".
* `apiUrl` (string): The Base API URL for TMT Analysis. Console display name: "Base URL".
* `city` (string): Value that will be matched against the city on file, generating a city name matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "City".
* `country` (string): Value that will be matched against the country on file, generating a country name matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "Country".
* `dataPoints` (string): Console display name: "".
* `day` (number): Day of birth. This parameter will be used with month and year to generate an overall matching score for DOB. Console display name: "DOB (Day)".
* `email` (string): Value that will be matched against the email on file,. Console display name: "Email".
* `first_name` (string): Value that will be matched against the first name on file, generating the matching score in the response. Console display name: "First Name".
* `last_name` (string): Value that will be matched against the last name on file, generating the matching score in the response. Console display name: "Last Name".
* `middle_name` (string): If middle name matching is available, the middle name matching score will be returned in the response. If middle name matching is not available, the submitted middle name will be matched with the submitted first_name and an overall first name match score will be returned. Console display name: "Middle Name".
* `month` (number): Month of birth. This parameter will be used with day and year to generate an overall matching score for DOB. Console display name: "DOB (Month)".
* `phoneNumber` (string): Phone Number that we want to extract information for. Console display name: "Phone Number".
* `postcode` (string): Value that will be matched against the postal code on file, generating a postal code matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "Post Code".
* `province` (string): Value that will be matched against the province on file, generating a province name matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "Province".
* `street` (string): Value that will be matched against the street name on file, generating a street name matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "Street Name".
* `street_no` (string): Value that will be matched against the street number on file, generating a street number matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "Street Number".
* `unit_name` (string): Value that will be matched against the unit name on file, generating a unit number matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "Unit Name".
* `unit_no` (string): Value that will be matched against the unit number (building number) on file, generating a unit number matching score where available, otherwise having a weight in the overall address matching score. Console display name: "Unit Number".
* `year` (number): Year of birth. This parameter will be used with month and day to generate an overall matching score for DOB. Console display name: "DOB (Year)".


